ere they get the closest. From what I have seen the GL only roams through there about every half hour.  I have gating/logged on in that spot many times.<br>
<br>
And as an FYI, I got this on my server by doing a week long raid.  The zone isn't that highly contested, and we got him twice in 5 days.  The hardest part is break in.  Once you are at NCamp you just gotta make sure you go back to camp at NC each night.  A single high-50's group can easily handle the zone, with only a minor worry to Golems and other mini's.  <br>
<br>
And the BG does spawn at the bell tower, almost exactly at the base of Fright's hill, so be careful.<br>
<br>
There are two very nice points made here, with the Bind Sight/Druid death tracking idea.  Course, in all honesty, the Druid tracking idea can be easily handled by a skilled Ranger.  There is only one druid on Quellious server I would choose over a ranger in Fear, cause Bippity rocks the zone like it was Crushbone. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://xtctripp101.homestead.com/files/Sigs/Ashrine_Sig.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
